# systemctl rescue

> Enter rescue mode.
> See also: `systemctl emergency`.
> More information: <https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/systemctl.html#rescue>.

- Enter rescue mode:

`systemctl rescue`

- Enter rescue mode asynchronously:

`systemctl rescue --no-block`
